  "body": "When defining/mixing in a custom method in a react component it loses all static properties:\n\n```\nvar customFunction = function(){\n  // Do magic\n}\ncustomFunction.myStaticProperty = \"some important value\";\n\nReact.createClass({\n  customFunction : customFunction,\n  render: function(){\n    this.customFunction.myStaticProperty // Undefined\n  }\n});\n\n```\n\nStatic properties are replaced by these four react properties:\n\n```\n this.customFunction.__reactBoundContext\n this.customFunction.__reactBoundMethod\n this.customFunction.__reactBoundArguments\n this.customFunction.bind\n```\n\nIs there a reason to remove the users static properties from methods? \nWould it be possible to **add** the react properties to the method â€“ keeping the custom properties in place?\n",
